25|$|The {{world of}} bull{{fighting}} {{is a key}} part of Lamborghini's identity. In 1962, Ferruccio Lamborghini visited the Seville ranch of Don Eduardo Miura, a renowned breeder of Spanish fighting bulls. Lamborghini, a Taurus himself, was so impressed by the majestic Miura animals that he decided to adopt a raging bull as the emblem for <b>the</b> <b>automaker</b> he would open shortly.|$|E
