25|$|Born 5 December 1928, in Buffalo, New York, Meyers {{attended}} {{public schools}} and in 1950 earned a Bachelor of Science in engineering and in 1954 a Master of Science magna cum laude in business from Carnegie Mellon University. He joined the Ford Motor Company in 1950, but his work at <b>the</b> <b>automaker</b> was cut by military service. Meyers was {{an officer in the}} U.S. Air Force during the Korean War.|$|E
